This paper focuses on improving reading comprehension tasks using neural methods, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically addresses the challenge of entity tracking, which is a common problem in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is dedicated to NLP research. 

The paper also proposes modifications to improve performance, which involves training neural models and optimizing objective functions. This suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Additionally, the paper uses multi-task learning, which involves training models on multiple related tasks simultaneously. This aligns with the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which focuses on neural networks and their applications. 

Finally, the paper involves analyzing and understanding the performance of neural models, which is related to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with search and retrieval of information.
